see protocol_is_too_hard_to_follow in the EGRE project.

All the protocol stuff for the src/rules in this MUD actually happen in the EGRE project.
We copy all the egre code here and then the parse_transform directives in the rules modules call out to the egre code.

Kicking off a fresh compile:

  ░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░
  ░
  ░ touch src/rules/*
  ░ export EGRE_PARSE_TRANSFORM_OUT_DIR=inlined_rules
  ░ ./c
  ░
  ░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░

After that, you find the inlined "scope path" files in inlined_rules/ and the events BERT files in events/

